The Office of Public Liaison is responsible for coordinating meetings and events to address requests from the American people and convey their messages to the President and other senior White House officials. They also organize listening sessions with leaders of organizations and businesses to understand and address the issues faced by average Americans. As an intern in the Office of Public Liaison, the author has witnessed the connection between the American people and the Executive Office of the President. They feel honored to be a part of helping the Office of Public Liaison respond to the needs of the American people.